        <h2 id="design-flexibility">Design and customisation</h2>
        <p>Shopify has a curated theme store with over 100 themes. Visual editing is straightforward. For customisation beyond what the theme offers, you need a Shopify developer familiar with Liquid, Shopify's templating language. Good Liquid developers in India are less common than WordPress developers, which can make custom development more expensive or slower.</p>
        <p>WooCommerce works with any WordPress theme. The developer talent pool in Ahmedabad and across Gujarat is large for WordPress. Customisation involves standard PHP, HTML, and CSS. For businesses needing a unique product configurator, a custom checkout flow, or complex membership systems, WooCommerce is significantly more practical.</p>

        <h2 id="scalability">Scalability</h2>
        <p>Shopify scales automatically. As your traffic grows, Shopify's infrastructure handles it. You do not worry about server capacity during a sale or a spike from an Instagram viral post.</p>
        <p>WooCommerce scalability depends on your hosting. Basic shared hosting handles a few hundred visitors per day. For serious e-commerce traffic, you need managed WordPress hosting (Cloudways, Kinsta, or SiteGround) at &#8377;2,000 to &#8377;6,000/month. This is manageable and still often cheaper than Shopify's higher plans, but it requires awareness and proactive management.</p>

        <h2 id="who-should-choose">The decision framework</h2>
        <p><strong>Choose Shopify if:</strong> You want to launch quickly without technical involvement. Your store is straightforward with standard products and standard checkout. You are comfortable with a higher ongoing cost in exchange for operational simplicity. You expect very high traffic and want zero infrastructure worry. You plan to sell internationally alongside India.</p>
        <p><strong>Choose WooCommerce if:</strong> You want to minimise ongoing platform costs. You have access to a WordPress developer or a web agency that manages it for you. You need deep SEO control. You need custom functionality. You want full ownership and portability of your store data. Your transaction volume makes the 2% platform fee difference meaningful.</p>
        <p>For most first-time Ahmedabad and Gujarat business owners building an online store with a setup budget below &#8377;75,000 and moderate transaction volumes: WooCommerce typically offers better long-term value. For businesses that need to launch in 2 weeks without any technical involvement and are willing to pay more for simplicity: Shopify is the right choice.</p>

